entry.title: Editor becomes blank when worker terminates even though script is available in other workers
entry.content:
Chrome Version: 125.0.6396.3 (Official Build) dev (64-bit)
Derived from issue 333945853.
# Steps to reproduce the problem 1. Visit https://stackblitz.com/edit/stackblitz-starters-hwlude 1. Open DevTools and click on Sources 1. Click CMD+P or equivalent to open a file 1. Search for blitz and open the one named `blitz.<hash>.js` 1. Search for `.Module.runMain(e.argv[1])` and put a breakpoint on that line 1. Head over to the terminal on the page and type in `node index.js` and hit enter 1. Wait for the debugger to pause in the script. 1. Resume execution 1. Wait for the worker to terminate and observe that the editor goes blank for the `blitz.<hash>.js` script.
The script is available in other workers. Closing the now empty tab and re-opening the blitz,<hash>.js` script in another worker shows the content again. Since we de-duplicate all the identical script into a canonical UISourceCode, the editor shouldn't go blank probably.

entry.title: Box model should support modern CSS like padding-block, margin-inline
entry.content:
Canary, see attached video for repro
1. Open DevTools > Elements > Select any element > Open Styles tab 2. Add **padding-block-start:14px** and **padding-inline: 20px** to the element 3. Expand the Computed tab. In the box model, edit the **padding-block-start** from 14 to 22. 4. The Styles tab shows a new **padding-top: 22px** rule. [NOT OK] 5. In the box model, edit **padding-inline-start** (the value on the left) from 20 to 50 6. The Styles tab shows another a new **padding-left: 50px** rules. [NOT OK]
**What is expected**
In step 4, I expect to see an updated rule **padding-block-start: 22px** instead of a new **padding-top** rule.
In step 6, I expect the same - DevTools should be smart enough to know I prefer to use modern CSS. I expect to see a new property **padding-inline-start: 50px** instead of **padding-left**
Same goes with `margin-{block,inline}`, `border-{block,inline}`
Perhaps another question for us is also should we encourage the usage of these modern css props than `top, bottom, left, right`.

entry.title: Edit box value return invalid value and multiple rules
entry.content:
Canary, see attached video for repro.
1. Open DevTools > Elements > Select any element > Open Styles tab > Expand Computed 2. In the box model, edit the margin-top field to **12px** 3. Observe a new rule **margin-top: 12px** is created in the Styles tab [OK] 4. In the box model, edit the margin-top field to **-** 5. Observe the rule **margin-top: 12px** is updated to **margin-top: -** in the Styles tab [MAYBE NOT OK] 6. In the box model, edit the margin-top field to **30px** 7. Observe another new rule **margin-top: 30px** is created in addition to **margin-top: -** in the Styles tab [NOT OK]
**What seems unexpected and what I expect**
a. Sometimes ago, ergunsh@ landed a CL to block editing invalid value in the Styles tab, we should extend the blocking to here too. E.g. If you try edit **margin-top: -** in the Styles tab, it won't let you.
b. In the box model, we show **-** as the default value, so it's natural for dev to type **-** when they want to reset the value, but in this case, **-** causes invalid value in the Styles tab
c. Multiple **margin-top** rules created during edit. I would expect DevTools to update the existing property but it keeps adding new one.

entry.title: chrome.scripting.executeScript with allFrames hangs when website uses Google Publisher Tags
entry.content:
# Steps to reproduce the problem 1. Visit chrome://settings/adPrivacy and ensure all three ads settings are enabled 2. Install the extension from the zip file and open the service worker console for it 3. Click on the browser action for this extension. 4. Two tabs will open, wait for them to finish loading. 5. The logs in service worker console will state:
""" Tab loaded for https://example.com/ Promise resolved for https://example.com/ Tab loaded for https://googleads.github.io/google-publisher-tag-samples/display-test-ad/js/demo.html """
Expected logs: a "Promise resolved" log for the googleads URL should also be printed Actual logs: "Promise resolved" log is never printed for the googleads URL
# Problem Description As seen in the repro steps, the promise for scripting.executeScript never resolves. It should at least resolve or reject.
Impact: this issue impacts all websites implementing google ads like espn.com or cnn.com
Note: The googleads page is the official sample implementation for the Google Publisher Tag library, see here: https://developers.google.com/publisher-tag/samples/display-test-ad Its source is very simple and is given here: https://github.com/googleads/google-publisher-tag-samples/blob/main/dist/display-test-ad/js/demo.html
Further analysis: the issue seems related to an intersection of adsPrivacy, fencedframe and allFrames. The following two observations suggest the issue requires a fencedframe specifically: (a) After step 4, deleting the `fencedframe` from inside `iframe[name=goog_topics_frame]` immediately resolves the promise. (b) changing allFrames: true to frameIds: [0] and then repeating steps 1-4 does not reproduce the issue. In fact, you can list out all the frameIds from the page and it will still not reproduce the issue.
The following two observations suggests the issue requires site targeted ads specifically: (a) In chrome://settings, disabling "Site-suggested ads" and "Ads measurement" from "Ads Privacy" section, and then repeating steps 1-4 does not reproduce the issue. (b) trying the issue on a fencedframe like so <fencedframe width="640" height="320"></fencedframe> (without any ad/auctions running) and then repeating steps 1-4 does not reproduce the issue (c) enabling an adblocker extension (like uBlock Origin) and then repeating steps 1-4 does not reproduce the issue.
# Additional Comments Component should be Platform>Extensions
# Summary chrome.scripting.executeScript with allFrames hangs when website uses Google Publisher Tags
# Custom Questions #### Which component does this fall under? Not sure - I don't know
#### Does this work in other browsers? Not sure - I don't know
# Additional Data Category: API \ Chrome Channel: Stable \ Regression: N/A

entry.title: Support mismatched and non-square icons
entry.content:
Context: b/335035467
https://wideo.co/pwa/login 's manifest (https://app.wideo.co/manifest.json) specifies its icons like ``` { "src": "https://resources.wideo.co/img/ng/pwa/wideo192x192.png", "type": "image/png", "sizes": "192x192", "purpose": "any maskable" }, ```
The icon itself is actually 193x192. All of its icons (that load) are 1px off in one of the dimensions. The mainfest spec (https://www.w3.org/TR/appmanifest) doesn't appear to have any problem with this.
Chrome currently discards all non-square and non-matching icon bitmaps. Chrome should instead resize icons to fit the "sizes" field specified in the manifest.
